[recto] Ad [Addendum] Wedding Dance in Open Air. J.G. van Gelder, Jan de Bisschop 1628-1671, Offprint; citaten pp. 12, 14, 15; [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. The drawing is not after Detroit version (very different proportions e.g. of the bride's curtain) but if it refers to an Arundel picture, it may well be "BREUGEL" "Balla de Contadini", or BREUGHEL "Festa de Contadini" rather than BREUGEL Fiera o feste de Contadini; [verso] (all printed [Mary] Cox, [Inventory of the Arundel Collection], Burl. Mag. CII, vol. XIX, Sept. 1911, p. 323).
